(59928, 397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This ship won\'t make it to the island in one piece.\n\nHold on to something, and pray that the elements will spare us from a grim death at sea.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(59927, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You show promise, $c. Perhaps you too will find glory on the island!', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(59926, 669, 397, 0, 0, 0, 259, 0, 0, 'Good, you\'ve kept training since we set sail.\n\nI need to speak with the crew about this storm. \n\nSpar with Throg. He will assess your skills and decide on your role once we make landfall.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(55509, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is a truly great thing you have accomplished this day. Be recognized for your sacrifice!', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(55511, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lok\'tar! Victory for the Horde!', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58452, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Even in the afterlife, the legend of Huln Highmountain continues to grow.\n\nYou have done well to secure his aid, $n. Now let our search begin.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58451, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The hunt is over. We have prevailed.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(59721, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are just in time. My preparations are nearly complete.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58449, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Reldorn hefts the sacs, which bulge uncomfortably.>$b$bSo many? Just how big is this thing you two are hunting, anyway?', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58450, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am amazed that this contains so much concentrated anima. You will surely lure a devourer to you with this!', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58447, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This problem just got a lot larger. We need a new plan.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58706, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. This confirms my suspicions.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(59258, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now, let us speak of the hunt.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58446, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, yes. I know of whom you speak.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58445, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thiernax suggests a bold plan. Locating the other former Night Warriors will not prove easy.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(61171, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If the Thornspeakers have no way to break the curse, then perhaps there truly is no hope for the possessed. These are tidings most dire.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(61711, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You performed the ritual admirably, but the Gorak Zhar\'s power was too strong for Gweyir to withstand. There is nothing more we can do, I am afraid.\n\nIt seems the masked fae are lost to us after all...', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(61710, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Though this bodes ill, I am not ready to give up hope that Ara\'lon survived. He may still be out there.\n\nI will assemble a search party. We will find him and bring him home... no matter what fate has befallen him. Thank you.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(61709, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This contains everything we need. Give me a moment and I will prepare the reagents for our ritual.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(61703, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, you were able to find enough nox root for the ritual. Unfortunately, we have another problem...', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(61143, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It feels good to be out of that cage and back home in my den.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(61702, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not a moment too soon! I appreciate your punctuality.\n\nMy den is not far away. We should hurry before more Drust arrive.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58773, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Drust locked me in this cage and dragged Kivarr away! If you release me, I can show you where they went!', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(61701, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ulfar sent you to find me? Free me from this cage, and I will do what I can to aid you.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(61113, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the place, but Kivarr is nowhere to be found...', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(61102, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kivarr... yes, I have heard of someone by that name. Ara\'lon may know where to find her.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(61076, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can sense Gorak Tul\'s dark power seething within this fetish. Handle it with caution, $c.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(61061, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have come from beyond the veil to seek my wisdom? A long journey indeed...', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(60934, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So Gweyir and Ara\'lon are the only survivors... this is grave news.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(60928, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gweyir is the only survivor... but she\'s already been afflicted by the Drust\'s cursed magic. \n\nWe can\'t just leave her here. Not like this!', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(60910, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes! We can use these masks to disguise ourselves.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(60898, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Keep your voice down. There are masked fae are nearby...', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(62428, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A majestic shape, for certain. It is now yours, should you choose to use it.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(62560, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re on the right track, $n! Keep doing what you\'re doing and it will be back to its full, glorious, starryness in no time!', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(59071, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Were it not for your aid, Qadarin\'s soul would have been lost forever.\n\nI... I can do no less than offer my aid in return.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(59069, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This figurine... I have not seen it since...\n\nI gave this to her when we first became Aspects. Our duties would draw us apart for the first time in our lives. To know that she has kept it all this time...\n\n<Ysera wipes her eyes.>\n\nWe will put it to good use.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(59068, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have no idea how tempted I am to open this and read it. Let\'s hurry up and create this counter-curse!', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(59070, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'HA! That will teach those spriggans! You mess with the mistrunner, you get the magical horn!\n\nNow we have the anima we need! And, conveniently, it\'s already attuned to the bad attitude of the one who cast the curse.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(59063, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew Dreyden would have the scroll we need. We don\'t have time to waste!', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(59725, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Please tell me you are here to help with the spriggan problem!', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58871, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I bet those spriggan thought this would be pretty funny. Well, we\'re not laughing!', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58704, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I should have never left! He\'s told me time and again that I should face my...\n\nNever mind. I can deal with that later.\n\nThe situation would have been much more dire if the two of you were not here.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully they\'ll get the message and go back from whence they came!', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58647, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. This task is much easier with help.\n\n<Qadarin sighs.>\n\nI hope you do not think too poorly of Thiernax. His history with the Night Warrior ritual is rife with misplaced guilt and remorse, but I am certain I can get him to see sense and offer his aid.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(59008, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Capturing souls is a far more brazen act than the typical spriggan prank. I wonder what has changed...', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58610, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Qadarin watches Thiernax race off. He sighs before turning to you.>\n\nMy apologies. Thiernax may have seemed curt, but there is a reason for his reluctance to speak of the Night Warrior.\n\nIf you have a moment to help me out in the garden, I can elaborate. Then I will see what can be done to convince Thiernax to help your mother.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(60246, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, what is this? It is so bulbous and squirming, it must be close to the next molting. I am something of an amateur gorm-breeder myself, and will find a proper place to raise this one. \n\nYou may trust that I intend to destroy no worlds, I give you my word.\n\nNow, I must tend to him, gather something from our stocks on your way out.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(58820, 574, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can feel their power. Perhaps they will give us the advantage we need.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(61869, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These belonged to the Primus!', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(59722, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s like we were never gone.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(61594, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is time to depart.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(61569, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Come, $p. Would you not witness your success firsthand?', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(61551, 113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your strength never fails to impress me.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(61548, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Expertly navigated. Perhaps you should pilot the necropolis.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(60112, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He ought to be here... but he isn\'t.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(61518, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems we\'ve been discovered. Times like these demand flexibility.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(61485, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us put our plan into motion.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(57778, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are pleased to see your return.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(62169, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, Maw Walker. The Eyes place their trust in you.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(60257, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This... is not what I expected.\n\nIt is similar in appearance to our people, yet so very different. Are there others of our kind out there? Who are they, and where do they reside? Why have they not made contact with us? Or are they hiding themselves purposefully?\n\nIs this a history we knew but have forgotten? I have so many questions.\n\nI thank you for this, it is quite meaningful to us. Please, take a relic of power from the treasury.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(59827, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your performance has netted me a nice profit... Zo\'umlo bet poorly.', 37176); -- -Unknown-
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(62867, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A very good collection of souls. Not too broken, not too drained, and not too innocent.\n\nNever fear, their fate is better in our hands than the Jailer\'s.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(60256, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now this is quite a find. A functional piece of the mysterious machinery that can be found around the Shadowlands.\n\nLook at how intricate the weaving of the golden orb is, how the energy seems to be contained from somewhere within, yet in a construct that is almost beyond imagining. What could have made such an object? Where are they now?\n\nWe shall begin to investigate with fervor. Do drop in if you find anything similar, and take a reward before you go.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(62739, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome! What brings you to the Heart of the Forest?', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(57571, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Denathrius may not have set the mirrors, but it\'s his fault I am here.\n\nThose that rouse his suspicion are sent here to suffer, even once loyal servants like myself.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(57532, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This must be some sort of mistake!', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(57531, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is it? Are you sure there wasn\'t more?', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(60276, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your reward, as promised.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(60470, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sabina\'s end has found her. Ash is all that remains.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(60468, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This looks like it could fit.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(60469, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'ve perished? Are you sure? Who could have done something so cruel...', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(60467, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sabina begins to stir. >\n\nAre... are they back? Help... help me.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(63037, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And to what do I owe the pleasure of a mortal visiting Revendreth at such an...inopportune time?', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(62279, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Revendreth would be most grateful for your aid.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(25073, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, young $r.$B$BYa come highly recommended, mon. It\'s nice ta finally be meetin\' ya in person.', 36949), -- Sen'jin Village
(24814, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tha power dat burst forth when tha Sea Witch died was immense. I can use dis power ta enact a vision of places far away.$B$BObserve, youngblood. I want ya ta be here when I make contact wit\' Thrall, perhaps it will be grantin\' ya insight as well.', 36949), -- An Ancient Enemy
(24813, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dat should keep dem at bay.', 36949), -- Territorial Fetish
(24812, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well fought, young $r.', 36949), -- No More Mercy
(25035, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to have ya, $G brotha:sista;.$B$BVol\'jin makes us all proud in dese moments. It feels good ta be tacklin\' threats head on.', 36949), -- Breaking the Line
(24626, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Swiftclaw! Kijara was tellin\' me about him and he sounded like he\'d be a handful. I don\'t mind da challenge - it\'s da spirited ones like dat that be makin\' da bravest and truest companions when real times of need be comin\'.$B$BTank ya, hon. Ya\'ve been very helpful.', 36949), -- Young and Vicious
(24625, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n! Dis naga has set us back quite some time, but nothin\' will be holdin\' us down foreva.$B$BIt\'s good ta be havin\' ya wit us, $n. Ya have a fierce heart within ya.', 36949), -- Consort of the Sea Witch
(24624, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c.$B$BIt will be takin\' brave and determined people like you ta drive da Darkspear up again. I hope dere are more people even half as dedicated to come.', 36949), -- Mercy for the Lost
(24623, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank ya so much! They can be vicious when provoked, but most of da time dey don\'t know betta.', 36949), -- Saving the Young
(24622, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice ta see new faces \'round here, mon. It\'s easy ta get ta feelin\' isolated since we left Orgrimmar.', 36949), -- A Troll's Truest Companion
(63145, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Quite the find, Maw Walker. Firsthand information from within Torghast is rare and valuable. None who set foot in the tower return to tell the tale.\n\nPresent company excluded, of course.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(56042, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'OUTPUT: Please accept this GIFT. \n\nADMINISTER GIFT DISTRIBUTION PROTOCOL.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(57929, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Decorous and deserved.\n\nI hope this will be the first of many corrupt inquisitors we fell together.', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(60128, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Temel has told me quite the tale of your previous adventures together, Maw Walker.', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(57926, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Archivist Fane\'s eyes light up when you hand him the archives.>\n\nThis is a lot of potential leverage...', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(60487, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yeah, these\'ll last me awhile.\n\nAlright, I\'ll show you the trick to making a barricade quickly...', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(57927, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Cryptkeeper Kassir inspects the pieces of Temel you brought him.>\n\nThey bashed you real good, didn\'t they, Temel? Nothing I cannot fix...', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(60127, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Cryptkeeper Kassir grins.>\n\nSo you finally listened to the Accuser, eh?\n\nBetter late than never.', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(57928, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The atonement crypts are meant to be used as storage for souls who require additional... processing before their next ritual.\n\nThe Lord Chamberlain\'s idiots are using them like prison cells and treasure rooms. You are doing us all a favor by opening them whenever you find a key.', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(57925, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Some very angry judges recently passed through here.\n\n<Archivist Fane grins.>\n\nTell me everything you did to antagonize them. Don\'t skip a single detail!', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(57924, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I sacrificed more than you realize to save this soul.\n\nI would do it again, because it is right. Do you understand yet?', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(57923, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Absolution does not come easy. Nor should it.', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(57921, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. You are ready for the ritual.', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(57922, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'His just reward would be the Maw, but this will have to do.', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(57920, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Every lost soul must be tended to.', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(58093, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am already working to undo the Lord Chamberlain\'s mistakes.\n\nYes, you may assist me.', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(61114, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This... This is from one of our own... from within the city walls.\n\nI will send word to our patrols. Remain alert, $n.\n\nShould the Scourge rise from within our own ranks, find me at once!', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60738, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m surprised that any wildseed could spawn such nightmares.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60520, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There, that seems to have calmed her. I can feel her dreams begin to ease.\n\nYou really do have a knack for this!\n\nBut I\'m worried that we\'re only buying time, and we need to do something more drastic.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60522, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, you have a spirit cradle! That will be quite useful, indeed.\n\nAssuming we can calm this chaos, of course. The wildseed you bonded with is having intense nightmares... and they\'re manifesting all over the grove!', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60632, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It cannot be easy for Korayn to hunt one of our own... but she is right. The forest is not safe so long as Lorkron lurks within it.\n\nWhat a terrible fate... both for those who become possessed, and those who must hunt them down.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60631, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have slain so many, and yet more remain. We must get to the heart of this evil and tear it out.\n\nIf we don\'t, then soon it could spread all across Ardenweald.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60630, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If it was not clear before, it is now. This is a personal hunt.\n\nWe will rid Ardenweald of this monster.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60628, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Only Ara\'lon and Lumera survived? The rest have fallen?\n\n<Korayn trembles with unbridled fury.> \n\nI will see to it that their bodies are retrieved. And this cannot go unpunished. We will avenge them all!', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60629, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found far more weapons than I expected.\n\nVery strange. How could they acquire so many of OUR blades?\n\n<Korayn appears troubled.>\n\nThey will be used against our enemies again, I swear it.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60521, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lady Moonberry said she would be sending a strong hand to help secure this grove.\n\nNow, how are you in a fight?', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60519, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gone so soon... the forest must be in even more dire straits than I realized.\n\n<Moonberry looks crestfallen for a moment before resolutely setting her hands on her hips.>\n\nWell, then we\'ll just have to help ease the Queen\'s burden. Then she\'ll have the time to grant you an audience!', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60724, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Shadows loom over the weald, harbingers of tragedy to come.\n\nThe river of fate flows swiftly, its currents inexorable. Where they lead... cannot yet be seen.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60709, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve lost so much. Why would anyone do this?', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60671, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The heart of the grove...\n\nWe have to get it back... for all those who have fallen.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60648, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Derawyn... I can\'t lose her too! We can use the animacones to save her!', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60647, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So many animacones lost... at least we were able to recover these.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60638, 4, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found more wildseeds! They\'re so weak... I can\'t stand to see them like this.\n\nWe need to finish this and bring them to Tirna Vaal as soon as possible.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60639, 18, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Korenth is... gone? And the heart of the grove has been taken?\n\nThen... then we have much to do.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60637, 66, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. I tried so hard to save them... but once that mask is on, there is no return.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60624, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We can\'t leave Heartwood Grove like this.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60600, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Shadows loom over Heartwood Grove. Things unseen crawl within the darkness.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60594, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Starlight shines within Dreamweaver, radiant and serene.\n\nAnd... two rivers meet in a lush delta. A wildseed and a mortal, both new to the forest. Bonded by spirit and by fate.\n\nLong has it been since the boughs beheld such an event. The weald will be watching.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60577, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The animacones! In this time of drought, we have to scrounge for every bit of anima we can get. Thank you.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60575, 273, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work. This should help get the Tranquil Pools back to normal.\n\nI admit, I had thought the worst when I couldn\'t find any of the tenders. I\'m glad they were only eaten by the local vegetation.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60563, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work. We mustn\'t stop tending to the wildseeds that the Winter Queen has chosen to be saved.\n\nNow, perhaps you can lend me a hand with another matter.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60567, 6, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Normally, I wouldn\'t require help from whatever race you are.\n\nAh... my apologies. That was rude.\n\nPlease understand that Ardenweald is home to souls from across all of the mortal realm. It\'s hard for me to keep track of every race that arrives here.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57816, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 'You\'re new, aren\'t you? Not a fae, not a soul, nor are you bound for a wildseed.\n\nAnd the droman sent you here to help me? Well, this just got very interesting.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57951, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'From acorns grow forests, from souls comes vital anima. Small though they be, on them our fates depend.\n\nThe forest sighs in gratitude.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57950, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gone! The bad spriggan is gone! Spirit Glen will be ours again.\n\nNow to leave. We have to leave.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57949, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Stolen! They stole the anima! They ran like crazy and...\n\nWait that\'s normal. They\'re always that bad. Stupid spriggans!', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57948, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found them! You found my friends! They have their forms!\n\nNow we have one last thing to do. One last thing!', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57947, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s this? What\'s this?\n\nThe Tall Tree has sent you to help us? Help us!', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57787, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Featherlight says you\'ve kept up your end of our deal. That\'s great to hear!\n\nI have some news to share about getting you an audience with the Queen.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60859, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s been a while since a new soul arrived in Ardenweald, so each one already here is precious to us.\n\nI\'ll be sure to let Lady Moonberry know of your heroic rescue efforts on her behalf. She might even decide she owes you a favor!', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60857, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Droman Krelnor sighs wearily as he reads the short list of wildseeds.>\n\nAt least a few will be relocated to Tirna Vaal.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60778, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was fun to watch! You had that bird ready to build a nest and raise hatchlings!\n\nOh, how I needed that laugh...', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60341, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If you can handle the spriggans, then perhaps I can give you some of the more interesting items on Lady Moonberry\'s agenda. Excellent!', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60763, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope that your arrival in Ardenweald is a sign that better times are on the horizon.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60338, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We haven\'t seen anyone come through the gateway in a very long time! Certainly not someone like you.\n\nWhat brings you to Ardenweald?', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(61716, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A troubling vision indeed. But we must not give up hope.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(61715, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Even through his scarred, molten visage, the emotion on Bolvar\'s face is plain.>\n\nMy daughter... here. I never thought...', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(59206, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am glad of your return, mortal.\n\nI pray you were successful in preventing the advent of war between Bastion and Maldraxxus.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60737, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The runeblade glows brighter as you approach an old stone altar.>', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(59011, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are struggling to hold the line. We need to act fast.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(59974, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot allow this wound to fester any longer. I will burn it closed here and now!', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(62654, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You return in one piece. And with not just Darion, but his father as well. You continue to succeed, Maw Walker.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(61190, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now to get you and your... associates out of here.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(59973, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot thank you enough, $n.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(59966, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My father... Alexandros Mograine. The Ashbringer.\n\nI... never expected to see him again.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(59962, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Keep up. We have little time.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
