(60150, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n! I am relieved you survived that realm of darkness.\n\nI am eager to hear the tale.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60149, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We may find a shared cause in the Purpose. It has sent you to us.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60148, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Finally, the Purpose may be guiding us again.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60129, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Could it be? An actual mortal being in the Eternal City? The Purpose be served!', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60871, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'These are grim tidings, $p. It seems the Banshee has aligned herself with a darker power than we know.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60932, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'It seems that eliminating the herald has slowed the Scourge\'s advance.\n\nWe will have to remain vigilant. Thank you for all you have done, $p.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60867, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With their numbers momentarily reduced, now is our chance to strike.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(62225, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank the Light, you have returned unharmed!\n\nWere you able to learn anything about what the cult is doing?', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60861, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<This news is rather unsettling.>', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(62185, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my gratitude.\n\nI assure you this will not be forgotten.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60843, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These should suffice.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60828, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our scouts report increased activity among the Cult of the Damned.\n\nI believe it is time we learn exactly what our fanatical friends are planning.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(62157, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They must be planning something. Though what, I cannot say.\n\nI will instruct our scouts to observe and report.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60003, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ll see to it they receive proper attention.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60169, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It appears we are making headway.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(59877, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You arrive just in time. Commander Gregor spoke highly of you.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60767, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will see to it that King Greymane and the Lord Commander receive these reports, though I fear this is only the beginning.\n\nThis courier has just brought us dire news from Icecrown.\n\nIt appears we are not the only ones under assault.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60766, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. We will need all the strength we can muster in the coming days.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(59876, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is far worse than we thought.\n\nCommander Gregor must be told of the true extent of the Scourge\'s resurgence.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60117, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, I was told to expect the arrival of a seasoned $c.\n\nLet\'s get to work.', 36710); -- -Unknown-
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(60116, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'We must find a way to rescue Anduin and the others. But in this moment, the safety of our citizens and our allies is our highest priority.\n\nAs such, I have reached out to those experienced in dealing with threats of this nature.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(60113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew you would not hesitate to answer the call, $n.\n\nI will be brief.', 36710), -- -Unknown-
(62611, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There, it\'s done. They should be driven back, if only for a while. I appreciate the help.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(28734, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ilthalaine sent you? He was wise to do so. I am indeed in need of help.', 37474), -- A Favor for Melithar
(62866, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent Maw Walker. Our armies here will grow stronger with each soul you return.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(60545, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good that you have arrived.\n\nWe need heroes like you in this dire hour.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(61855, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you again, $p.\n\nYour continued dedication to the well-being of Ardenweald has not gone unnoticed.\n\nQadarin has expressed interest in taking a more active role. Let\'s put his skills to use, shall we?', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(60414, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, this is quite a find. These will allow me to procure some rather rare ingredients and materials, and with them, we may turn the tide against our foes. Well done.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(60381, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our bonds are stronger, our roots grow deeper, due to your actions this day. We will hold strong against the onset of foes that plague us, as groves weave together in defense, thanks to you.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(57652, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It really is a remarkable substance. We use it in practically everything! Construction, mending, crafts, and it can even be added to rations.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(63072, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fascinating, the metal here seems to be fabricated entirely of stygia!\n\nThere is much I can do with this. Take this reward, with my thanks.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(62286, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fascinating. Fascinating indeed. The Observer will be pleased.', 37474), -- -Unknown-
(62261, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see Guillotine\'s \"negotiations\" were successful.\n\nThank you, Maw Walker. These sharpening stones will be useful.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(59293, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He\'s smelly again? We\'ll at least he\'s happy, even if we are not.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(58992, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, if this isn\'t the best batch of marrow I\'ve ever seen! \n\nMama is going to cook you a feast today!', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(59828, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your performance has netted me a nice profit... Zo\'umlo bet poorly.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(62294, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is simply marvelous! This will provide some excellent insight into the history of Margrave Sin\'dane... and possibly something we can use to our own benefit later on.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(60251, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can only decipher a few words of this missive, give me a moment.\n\nIt appears to be a warning from the Margrave to another lord of Maldraxxus, or perhaps another place.\n\nI see mention of the Primus, and discussion of his fate. Or someone else\'s? It is hard to tell. It appears to point to a location, but I cannot understand the description of the location.\n\nThis may be more valuable than you know for the fate of the Shadowlands. Choose a reward, I will continue my work on this.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(60255, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This mask is similar in features to some of the automaton parts we have found in our time here in the Shadowlands. Perhaps it belonged to an ancient civilization? The information we have is scattered and incomplete.\n\nAny further pieces you may find of this sort will help us unravel these great mysteries. There seems to be a greater design to this place than we can see, yet so much of it eludes us.\n\nI will take it off of your hands, in exchange you make take one of our most valuable pieces.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(62403, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A fine amount. There will surely be something useful in this collection.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(58525, 378, 11, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'You found them! What wonderful insight into the minds of the venthyr.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(62194, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have helped strengthen our forces, Maw Walker.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(62217, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You and Marz work well together. He\'ll take the hit whenever you need him to.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(62213, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew the Maw Walker would deliver.', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(60291, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Rathan gives Flytrap an apprehensive look.>\n\nThat\'s... that\'s great!\n\nThank you both for bringing back these resources!\n\n<Rathan flashes you a nervous smile.>', 37176), -- -Unknown-
(60283, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p. Your contribution has been logged in our records for posterity to appreciate!', 37142), -- -Unknown-
(58395, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Maldraxxus is sworn to defend Revendreth from outside invaders, not siphon off our anima.\n\nAccept this gift for your role in bringing this conspiracy to light, $p.\n\nWe will need time to calculate our next move, but I am certain that you will be a key part of it.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58394, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It was unlikely that she\'d tell us anything useful, but I had to try.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58393, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The bigger they are... the bigger the explosion at the end. Ha!', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58392, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Traitors and cowards. I have time for neither!', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58391, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A lich? So close?\n\nCan you feel its presence? I once could...', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58389, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Blackbale venthyr are wielding the weapons of the Maldraxxi army?\n\nThat would mean...', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58518, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A lich?! The Tithelord is working with a lich from Maldraxxus?!\n\nHow? To what ends?\n\n<The Accuser composes herself.>\n\nDo you appreciate how troubling this is, $p?\n\nThis has never happened. This is not supposed to happen.\n\nPrince Renathal will know what to do.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58388, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did any of the Blackbale venthyr show signs of regret?\n\nWe had hoped to recruit some to our cause eventually.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58443, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re ready to begin our next lesson.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58387, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot comfortably call this a success, but it is likely the best outcome we could have hoped for. Carrying one\'s sins is no small feat, yet it can be liberating.\n\nTake this chain, if you wish, to display your commitment to owning your own sins. Kael\'thas needs it no longer.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58385, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kael\'thas Sunstrider may be ready for the ritual of absolution now.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58386, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I do not expect Kael\'thas to agree or even understand the value of mercy immediately.\n\nAbsolution is a long, slow process. This was only the first step.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58384, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I must admit, I did not expect the dredgers to be quite so eager to fight for their own freedom.\n\nThe Prince inspires all of us, I suppose.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58426, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m pleased you came. Let\'s begin.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58383, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To be clear: We did not absolve Kael\'thas Sunstrider of any of these sins.\n\nHe might never be absolved of them. It must ultimately be his choice to change.\n\nBut we did stabilize his soul, which means he will at least have the opportunity to make that choice.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(58382, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It shall not be easy to redeem Kael\'thas Sunstrider, and the outcome is far from guaranteed.\n\nBut we must attempt it nonetheless.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(61077, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I make no presumption that all mortals from Azeroth know each other. \n\nWhen confronting a challenging soul like this, however, it helps to offer even the faintest of familiarity.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(62308, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have proven yourself worthy to don the mantle, acolyte.\n\nWear it with honor and pride.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(62320, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It brings me great relief that your pallid vestments will no longer offend my vision.\n\nDo try keep them in better repair henceforth.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(62317, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sorcerer Vutral has been silenced, and with him the suspicions of your ruse.>', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(62297, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, acolyte. The rest should dissipate with time.\n\nTake this, it was left behind by the feckless adept that created this mess. I hope you will put it to better use.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(62363, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I must thank you. We are no match for the Chosen when it comes to brute strength.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(61962, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'I shall wield my blade with purpose once more!\n\nDeath to your enemies!', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(61729, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rahel has arrived from Darkhaven to assist us with, and I quote, \"killing anybody.\" She is quite eager to enter the fray.\n\nShe seemed rather upbeat at the prospect of working with you again, $p.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(60249, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A strange bauble, likely from another world. Yet, why would the paragon have brought this with her? \n\nPerhaps when carrying the soul of a child, as a reminder of something she had thought lost within herself? I will ponder this.\n\nYou may choose a reward from our stores.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(60184, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You do not cease to impress.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(60393, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are one step closer to returning our supply of souls to a functioning form, Maw Walker. This is an important advancement in the war for Maldraxxus.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(62966, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am heartened to know that Thrall yet lives. By the Light, we will find him.\n\nI fear for Anduin. Darkness hungers for his soul.\n\nWe must make ready. You will hear from me when it is time to proceed.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(62457, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, you succeeded where others, myself included, have failed.\n\nFrom what I hear, that\'s the second time a relic of the First Ones responded to your presence.\n\nI must admit, I haven\'t the slightest idea how you managed it. Interesting. Very interesting indeed.', 36949), -- -Unknown-
(61959, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'I shall pay my debt to my Maw Walker.\n\nDirect my power against your enemies.', 36839), -- -Unknown-
(63133, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, I have not seen these runes used in quite some time. An ancient broker method of encryption.\n\nThis will be useful should I ever intercept cartel communications.', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(60722, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes! I feel the flow of anima. You will want to return to the device periodically and channel more.\n\nAs you gather and channel more anima to a tower, its connection to our sanctum will grow stronger. Eventually you will be able to reinforce the channel, making it permanent.\n\nWith enough anima flowing throughout Maldraxxus, our armies will be unstoppable!', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(63057, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Long have I waited to weave anima across Maldraxxus once more.', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(63134, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Valuable information, indeed. This will help me avoid detection whenever I must leave the safety of the refuge.\n\nI trust you\'ve already committed the patrols to memory, Maw Walker.', 36753), -- -Unknown-
(57380, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This bad paper look very bad...', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57240, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You no go here. Here for bad buds!', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(59256, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This medallion will serve us well. But we lack our leader to don it.\n\nWe must seek out more allies.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(59209, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our numbers are bolstered. Our survival chance is only slightly less grim.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57189, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sounds like it worked better than expected. \n\nPerfect. The Fearstalker stands no chance.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57190, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The devourers will rip them to shreds.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60313, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am glad you made it here alive.\n\nGeneral Draven has informed me of a plan that might just work.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57159, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We barely made it. Denathrius will surely be on our trail soon.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60506, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We meet again. Under dire circumstances I fear.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57136, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. The fear we struck allowed us to extract ample anima for Revendreth.\n\nOnto our final target.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57164, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Once you master fear, all crumble before you.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57131, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Perhaps in death you will make a fine hunter.\n\nI can practically taste the fear we will inflict.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(59014, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us begin, shall we?', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58941, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that Duskterror is captured, we have a little more control over these grounds.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58916, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This soul is nearly ready. \n\nWe have an opportunity to finish preparing this one and take care of a problem in the process.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57098, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to the Grove of Terror.\n\nHere you will see the beginning of the process for the anima you seek.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(59232, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am nothing if not merciful and understanding.\n\nThe Accuser will be given every opportunity to repent her errors and learn from them.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57182, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sire Denathrius smiles as you hand him the medallion.>\n\nI am pleased to see that you can be trusted with great power.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57180, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lord Chamberlain smiles wryly.>\n\nThe Halls of Atonement are under my control.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57176, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is, in fact, one of the larger sinstones I have seen.\n\nThis will be easy to exploit.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(59023, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lord Chamberlain confirmed the kill. We should hurry.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57175, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As Echelon holds the sinstone fragments, anima binds draw the pieces into one another, reforming into a completed sinstone.>\n\nWe are ready to proceed.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(59021, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The ward on the Accuser\'s sinstone is weakened by the inquisitor\'s death.\n\nBut we must kill both inquisitors before the ward will fully fall, and we can access the Accuser\'s sinstone.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58932, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Echelon eyes Temel suspiciously.>\n\nI never liked this runt.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58931, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Temel will know how to exploit this sinstone.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57173, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is that truly the best you have to offer?', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57161, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Echelon grunts.> You\'re late.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57179, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now, Maw Walker, arise as a weapon of ordained power within my dominion.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57178, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wait! Please, Maw Walker, allow me to announce you to the Master.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58654, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, the peasants have asked for help have they? \n\nThose who are loyal would know that sacrifices are essential to the survival of Revendreth. Yes, these are dark times with anima and new souls both being in short supply. \n\nBut we must all do our part, no matter how painful.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57174, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is all that remains of our tithe? The Tithelord is not one for excuses. We may need to gather a second tithe quickly or he will condemn us all to the Ember Ward.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(56978, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It may not look like it, but this rebellion is on its last leg. Those who stand against the Master are fools who will know a new form of pain and suffering.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58433, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, mortal. Stoneborn require anima to exist. Without it, they return to their stone form. This supply hurt them more than destroying thirty of their rebels.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(56955, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your talents in combat show promise. Perhaps with a few more centuries and a little humility we might make something of you.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(56942, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are not getting the carriage through that.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(56829, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah good. No one got ate.\n\nCarriage is ready to go when you are.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57381, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was FUN! I have not felt so alive in centuries. Everything about you is just... different, and invigorating.\n\nI can continue to assist you until you are ready to leave the Endmire but then we will need to part ways for a time. I have some unfinished business regarding someone who put me in a cage.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57007, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh good, still not dead yet?\n\nYou see where the Lord Chamberlain or Cudgelface landed?', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57026, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully these wretched creatures did not bore you with their inane babble.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(57025, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sorry for the state of things. Usually a venthyr would be here to greet you. Been a while since we seen anyone come through that gate.\n\nAll good, though, as I know the welcome speech better than a good mornin\' whipping.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58724, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What has transpired in Ardenweald? Tell me everything.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(62807, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Many cries call in the night. Many creatures seek shelter.\n\nThis is a refreshing breeze.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58723, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Banished One stirs and Ardenweald\'s power withers in drought.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58721, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Winter Queen turns her gaze upon you.>\n\nHow curious to see someone like you in my forest.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60661, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well met, stranger. You arrive in... interesting times.\n\n<Herne snorts a laugh.>\n\nAnd with equally interesting company.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58869, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have won the battle...\n\n...But I fear we may have lost Ysera.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60621, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This attack... It is like they are being driven!', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58720, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These Drust thought to send a force to strike us from behind. \n\n<Korayn smirks.>\n\nYour call brought my fellow huntsmen and huntresses to reinforce us. Our foes were the ones caught by surprise.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58719, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Wild Hunt rides to our aid... but not from the west?\n\nThat is where Hunt-Captain Korayn was tracking a dangerous foe. She and her hunting party must have been waylaid.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58714, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These Drust are bold to send spies into my grove! Very bold... and very foolish.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58593, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a terrible end for such a majestic spirit... \n\nBut that was why she connected with you! Because you are of the same world! Azeroth!\n\nNow, I can finally feel her nightmares wane. At last, she knows some peace.\n\nThank you, my friend.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58590, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We all start somewhere. Sometimes in unexpected places. Me, I just popped out of the ground like a flower.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60578, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To have an old friend turn against you, in the most terrible way. How very painful. \n\nBut we are so close now, to soothing the spirit within the wildseed.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58591, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is just the beginning of their attack. But it is still a heavy blow dealt to them. Thank you.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58589, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re a natural at this. Now we can bring the spirit\'s nightmares into the open and deal with them directly.\n\nIf we succeed, she will be so much more at peace.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58592, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those Drust really are cruel to us fae! Those spirit tenders were just trying to do their job...\n\nThank you for helping them.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60572, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re ready to begin preparing for the ritual? Wonderful.\n\nI am also ready!', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58524, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found and took their anima right from the heart of the grove? Impressive.\n\nDreamweaver will be most pleased. But I expect that we will soon encounter some unhappy visitors.\n\nWe must move quickly to aid the spirit in this wildseed... before we are overrun.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58488, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that we have the heart, we need to find a way out of this place.\n\nAnd I hear the distinct sound of approaching enemies...', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58486, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We made it to the heart. Well done.\n\nIf that is what all the Drust are truly like, then Ardenweald is in a dire situation, indeed.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58480, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Drust have stolen more anima than I expected. To think that they have deprived us of this much in the midst of a drought...\n\nWe must take back whatever we can. Not only for the sake of the wildseed, but to also thwart whatever the Drust intend to do.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58483, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you.\n\nI know these are just objects, but they mean so much. Sometimes just holding a piece of one\'s past can be a comfort.\n\nIt means not everything is lost.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58484, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This anima will help Dreamweaver complete his ritual... and perhaps save spirits who otherwise would have been lost.\n\nGood work.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(58473, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I never thought I would return to Tirna Noch. The place of so many memories. So many regrets...\n\nBut now is not the time for sentimentality. Now is the time for action.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60905, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s going to be difficult, but I know of a place where there may be enough anima to help this wildseed.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60901, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dreamweaver has told me much about your strange wildseed. \n\nI will do what I can to help.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60881, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to see part of the Wild Hunt\'s strength restored... and also that you found the spirit cradle of use.\n\nNow let us bring the wildseed within it to Hibernal Hollow.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60856, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work, $n. This won\'t win our war... but it will at least help us in the fight for Soryn\'s Meadow.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60839, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for rescuing my fellow hunters. We\'ll have time to respect those who have returned to the cycle when this is all over.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60764, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to see you again. The Wild Hunt could use your help.', 36734), -- -Unknown-
(60869, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'This is troubling news, $p. To think that Sylvanas would willingly ally with such a dark power...', 36665), -- -Unknown-
(62163, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am glad for your return, $n.', 36665); -- -Unknown-
